      Cell[
       TextData["Convergents"]], "paclet:ref/Convergents"},
     "RefLink",
     BaseStyle->{"DefinitionBox", CellFrame -> 0}], Cell["\<\
Returns the convergents corresponding to a continued fraction\
\>", "TechNoteTableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "1d141bcf-e6f3-4474-a417-73c8ac7d4557"]}
  }]], "DefinitionBox",
 CellID->258195911,ExpressionUUID->"efc3ec2d-a893-4e5c-8979-4f57690b0f17"],

Cell["Functions used in the order-finding algorithm.", "TechNoteCaption",
 CellID->1581709237,ExpressionUUID->"818afa4d-c748-47be-b518-6c3ff9fb4fc6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Quantum Modular Exponentiation", "TechNoteSection",
 CellTags->"Section11",
 CellID->115979312,ExpressionUUID->"aa65fd00-f8d3-4a4a-b643-04898ea7f8d3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The order-finding problem is a specific case of the ",
 ButtonBox["period-finding problem",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/PeriodFindingAlgorithm"],
 ", where function ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["f", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "81a6d1f5-65ea-4d07-bf53-1a09d572de82"],
 " is not specified explicitly, but the corresponding quantum oracle is \
assumed to be implemented efficiently."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1496628955,ExpressionUUID->"210be481-b8e5-4637-a6fa-c67f7f1bc0f8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tUnlike the ",
 ButtonBox["period-finding algorithm",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/PeriodFindingAlgorithm"],
 ", the order-finding algorithm does not resort to quantum oracle but to ",
 ButtonBox["conditional exponentiation",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/ControlledPower"],
 ". Or, putting it another way, the quantum oracle corresponding to the ",
 ButtonBox["modular exponentiation",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/PowerMod"],
 " is efficiently implemented by the conditional exponentiation,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->366889374,ExpressionUUID->"58516b71-20ed-48de-82f2-7cbb92175903"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"x"},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{"y"},
      "Ket"]}], "\[RightTeeArrow]", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"x"},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["U", "x"], 
       TemplateBox[{"y"},
        "Ket"]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bae62041-6b94-45bf-a4f8-4d9e2c836732"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->884158281,ExpressionUUID->"26ba8f76-121d-43eb-8a86-1993ce981ed0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "of the quantum-adapted ",
 StyleBox[ButtonBox["modular multiplication",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/ModMultiply"],
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ","
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1608875174,ExpressionUUID->"2e7c118c-edb4-43c5-8430-f22a83a1ae81"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"U", ":", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"y"},
      "Ket"], "\[RightTeeArrow]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       RowBox[{"a", " ", "y", " ", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{"mod", " ", "N"}], ")"}]}]},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c6bfb1e8-2b63-4d43-98d8-bafd63948e78"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1398450041,ExpressionUUID->"da49374c-1250-484e-8088-f6ca6f8d8a6c"],

Cell["\<\
Note that repeated application of the modular multiplication gives the \
quantum adaptation of the modular exponentiation,\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1688806319,ExpressionUUID->"941c20bb-906b-4142-abf3-8ae7b06061f5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["U", "x"], 
     TemplateBox[{"y"},
      "Ket"]}], "\[RightTeeArrow]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox["a", "x"], " ", "y", " ", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{"mod", " ", "N"}], ")"}]}]},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dcb2f04f-a80f-4f18-be73-371a98d3caf3"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->476441034,ExpressionUUID->"839a5334-aac9-46b3-9310-90fa38c44ceb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Therefore, the order-finding algorithm is essentially the ",
 ButtonBox["quantum phase estimation",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/QuantumPhaseEstimation"],
 " for the modular multiplication."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1725422422,ExpressionUUID->"70865436-9811-4e05-9875-d262b05d315a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Implementation", "Subsection",
 CellID->1436481278,ExpressionUUID->"f19c9cac-0697-4e35-9aed-6ac5054d004d"],

Cell["\<\
As we will see below, the overall performance of the order-finding algorithm \
relies crucially on the fact that the modular exponentiation can be \
implemented efficiently on a quantum computer (Vedral et al., 1996). Here, \
let us take a look at the basic idea.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1031269061,ExpressionUUID->"7c8209bc-1d68-4257-9a43-5903ba06521f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tLet ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["V", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "228aec17-81de-4c07-b7cb-d2e8f80f034a"],
 " be the modular multiplication on two registers (to be compared with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["U", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bf850698-7d67-498e-b5d2-2407ca3b7b35"],
 " with fixed ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["a", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1e13aad2-f968-418a-a7fe-1c54337821da"],
 "),"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1460169106,ExpressionUUID->"f98ee866-347c-4ff6-a630-04a3ca9ddfd5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"V", ":", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"x"},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{"y"},
       "Ket"]}], "\[RightTeeArrow]", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"x"},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{
        RowBox[{"x", " ", "y", " ", 
          RowBox[{"(", 
            RowBox[{"mod", " ", "N"}], ")"}]}]},
       "Ket"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "221d1914-398c-42ec-bcf4-7b962dbf2d74"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1766530273,ExpressionUUID->"5dfdf8c2-2598-4450-8a1d-7e580c074b99"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The idea is to duplicate the logical state, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"x"},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{"0"},
      "Ket"]}], " ", "\[RightTeeArrow]", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"x"},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{"x"},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c07f1a6a-ff3f-430b-8884-f807f1e791e6"],
 " by employing the ",
 ButtonBox["CNOT gate",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/TwoQubitGates#1585062394"],
 ", and then to apply the modular multiplication on the two registers, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"x"},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{"x"},
      "Ket"]}], " ", "\[RightTeeArrow]", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"x"},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "(", 
         RowBox[{"mod", " ", "N"}], ")"}]},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5ad05b31-f0e5-433b-98fe-7de20a5efe76"],
 ". Repeating the procedure ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["k", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "957e7630-9d8b-4426-b93c-af2807553ad2"],
 " times produces the desired result. For example, the quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/OrderFindingAlgorithm#1881571407"],
 " below effectively performs ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["V", 
    SuperscriptBox["2", "3"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ef92891e-1ef9-4f35-983c-93bdede8c976"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1112878536,ExpressionUUID->"c6b11a64-763c-4bdd-a235-004997f187a0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 GraphicsBox[{
   {Dashing[{Small, Small}], LineBox[{}]}, 
   LineBox[{{{0, -1}, {7, -1}}, {{0, -2}, {7, -2}}, {{0, -3}, {7, -3}}, {{
    0, -4}, {7, -4}}}], InsetBox[
    TemplateBox[{"x"},
     "Ket"], {-0.2, -1.}, NCache[
    ImageScaled[{1, Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{1, 0.5}]], Automatic, {1, 
    0}], {InsetBox[
     TemplateBox[{"0"},
      "Ket"], {-0.2, -2.}, NCache[
     ImageScaled[{1, Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{1, 0.5}]], Automatic, {1, 
     0}], InsetBox[
     TemplateBox[{"0"},
      "Ket"], {-0.2, -3.}, NCache[
     ImageScaled[{1, Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{1, 0.5}]], Automatic, {1, 
     0}], InsetBox[
     TemplateBox[{"0"},
      "Ket"], {-0.2, -4.}, NCache[
     ImageScaled[{1, Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{1, 0.5}]], Automatic, {1, 
     0}]}, {LineBox[{{1, -1}, {1, -2}}], 
    DiskBox[{1, -1}, 0.09], {CircleBox[{1, -2}, 0.26666666666666666], 
     LineBox[{{{0.7333333333333334, -2}, {1.2666666666666666`, -2}}, {{
        1, -2.2666666666666666`}, {1, -1.7333333333333334`}}}]}}, {
    {LightDarkSwitched[
      GrayLevel[1]], EdgeForm[Opacity[1]], 
     RectangleBox[{1.6, -2.4}, {2.4, -0.6}]}, InsetBox[
     StyleBox["\<\"V\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontSize->Scaled[0.05714285714285714],
      FontWeight->"Light",
      FontSlant->Italic], {2., -1.5}, NCache[
     ImageScaled[{Rational[1, 2], Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{0.5, 0.5}]], 
     Automatic, {1, 0}]}, {LineBox[{{3, -2}, {3, -3}}], 
    DiskBox[{3, -2}, 0.09], {CircleBox[{3, -3}, 0.26666666666666666], 
     LineBox[{{{2.7333333333333334`, -3}, {3.2666666666666666`, -3}}, {{
        3, -3.2666666666666666`}, {3, -2.7333333333333334`}}}]}}, {
    {LightDarkSwitched[
      GrayLevel[1]], EdgeForm[Opacity[1]], 
     RectangleBox[{3.6, -3.4}, {4.4, -1.6}]}, InsetBox[
     StyleBox["\<\"V\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontSize->Scaled[0.05714285714285714],
      FontWeight->"Light",
      FontSlant->Italic], {4., -2.5}, NCache[
     ImageScaled[{Rational[1, 2], Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{0.5, 0.5}]], 
     Automatic, {1, 0}]}, {LineBox[{{5, -3}, {5, -4}}], 
    DiskBox[{5, -3}, 0.09], {CircleBox[{5, -4}, 0.26666666666666666], 
     LineBox[{{{4.733333333333333, -4}, {5.266666666666667, -4}}, {{
        5, -4.266666666666667}, {5, -3.7333333333333334`}}}]}}, {
    {LightDarkSwitched[
      GrayLevel[1]], EdgeForm[Opacity[1]], 
     RectangleBox[{5.6, -4.4}, {6.4, -2.6}]}, InsetBox[
     StyleBox["\<\"V\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontSize->Scaled[0.05714285714285714],
      FontWeight->"Light",
      FontSlant->Italic], {6., -3.5}, NCache[
     ImageScaled[{Rational[1, 2], Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{0.5, 0.5}]], 
     Automatic, {1, 0}]}, InsetBox[
    TemplateBox[{"x"},
     "Ket"], {7.2, -1.}, NCache[
    ImageScaled[{0, Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{0, 0.5}]], Automatic, {1, 
    0}], InsetBox[
    TemplateBox[{
      TemplateBox[{
        TemplateBox[{"\"x\"", "2"}, "Superscript", SyntaxForm -> 
         SuperscriptBox], "\" (mod N)\""}, "RowDefault"]},
     "Ket"], {7.2, -2.}, NCache[
    ImageScaled[{0, Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{0, 0.5}]], Automatic, {1, 
    0}], InsetBox[
    TemplateBox[{
      TemplateBox[{
        TemplateBox[{"\"x\"", "4"}, "Superscript", SyntaxForm -> 
         SuperscriptBox], "\" (mod N)\""}, "RowDefault"]},
     "Ket"], {7.2, -3.}, NCache[
    ImageScaled[{0, Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{0, 0.5}]], Automatic, {1, 
    0}], InsetBox[
    TemplateBox[{
      TemplateBox[{
        TemplateBox[{"\"x\"", "8"}, "Superscript", SyntaxForm -> 
         SuperscriptBox], "\" (mod N)\""}, "RowDefault"]},
     "Ket"], {7.2, -4.}, NCache[
    ImageScaled[{0, Rational[1, 2]}], ImageScaled[{0, 0.5}]], Automatic, {1, 
    0}]},
  ImagePadding->{{38.160000000000004`, 74.16}, {7.2, 7.2}},
  ImageSize->360,
  PlotRange->{{0, 7}, {-4.5, -0.5}},
  PlotRangePadding->Scaled[0.025]]], "Picture",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 CellID->1714472829,ExpressionUUID->"ba10dca5-f992-438d-a30a-05cf63efd513"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 2",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". A heuristic quantum circuit to implement the modular exponentiation. Each \
horizontal line denotes a register of ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " qubits (not a single qubit) so that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"x", "=", "0"}], ",", "1", ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["2", "n"], "\[Minus]", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"e19c80ef-d3b8-42d8-8211-2b262b5008b2"],
 ", and label ",
 StyleBox["V",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " indicates the quantum-adapted modular multiplication."
}], "TechNoteCaption",
 CellID->1881571407,ExpressionUUID->"56955f42-1de1-4482-9e08-f9cbfc1b8be5"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Quantum Implementation", "TechNoteSection",
 CellTags->"Section12",
 CellID->1702961113,ExpressionUUID->"c3cc814b-15aa-4abc-bd85-3543781f0f0f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let us now formulate the order-finding problem more precisely in the form \
of ",
 ButtonBox["quantum phase estimation",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/QuantumPhaseEstimation"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->5378975,ExpressionUUID->"435b3a71-0dd5-47ee-ad06-505e1494f5ae"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tApplying the modular multiplication ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["r", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f1121e1f-88a1-42b8-9a3a-ec2bf84928e1"],
 " times on a fixed state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"1"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fabf61b3-1382-415b-8a8b-60bb48f26424"],
 " should bring the system back to the original state. Therefore, the quantum \
states"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->210119651,ExpressionUUID->"62727848-1c0b-486c-9411-768a6d8f52fa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"], ",", "  ", 
    RowBox[{"U", 
     TemplateBox[{"1"},
      "Ket"]}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["U", "2"], 
     TemplateBox[{"1"},
      "Ket"]}], ",", " ", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["U", 
      RowBox[{"r", "-", "1"}]], 
     TemplateBox[{"1"},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "713a96ee-d429-4d76-9081-c69648713668"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1017858689,ExpressionUUID->"71d1ea2d-41bf-46b8-9baa-ad286c4c618e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "form a closed cycle. In physics, it is common to construct the eigenstates \
of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["U", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e4a1c0f5-7812-4cde-91ea-15b627540de7"],
 " that generates the cycle with the discrete Fourier transform of those \
quantum states in the sequence. By definition, the latter is the ",
 ButtonBox["quantum Fourier transform",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/QuantumFourierTransform"],
 ". Indeed, define"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->296254021,ExpressionUUID->"fd797894-e395-4f1a-8ed6-ab73337a0b7c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "k"]},
     "Ket"], ":=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       SqrtBox["r"]], 
      UnderoverscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
       RowBox[{"x", "=", "0"}], 
       RowBox[{"r", "-", "1"}]], 
      SuperscriptBox["U", "x"], 
      TemplateBox[{"1"},
       "Ket"], 
      SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
       RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", "\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "x", " ", 
        RowBox[{"k", "/", "r"}]}]]}], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       SqrtBox["r"]], 
      UnderoverscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
       RowBox[{"x", "=", "0"}], 
       RowBox[{"r", "-", "1"}]], 
      TemplateBox[{
        RowBox[{
          SuperscriptBox["a", "x"], " ", 
          RowBox[{"(", 
            RowBox[{"mod", " ", "N"}], ")"}]}]},
       "Ket"], 
      SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
       RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", "\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "x", " ", 
        RowBox[{"k", "/", "r"}]}]]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e652b377-7fd3-4786-8709-cc92d43f4275"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1274237201,ExpressionUUID->"aec298de-392d-40c4-9c8a-9c968e69a396"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"k", "=", "0"}], ",", "1", ",", "...", ",", 
    RowBox[{"r", "\[Minus]", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "953ada66-4341-4b46-87ba-56686075c099"],
 ". We see that"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1397709323,ExpressionUUID->"14811182-de76-4713-a036-4e6cfbb4e9a0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"U", 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "k"]},
      "Ket"]}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       SqrtBox["r"]], 
      UnderoverscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
       RowBox[{"x", "=", "0"}], 
       RowBox[{"r", "-", "1"}]], 
      TemplateBox[{
        RowBox[{
          SuperscriptBox["a", 
           RowBox[{"x", "+", "1"}]], " ", 
          RowBox[{"(", 
            RowBox[{"mod", " ", "N"}], ")"}]}]},
       "Ket"], 
      SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
       RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", "\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "x", " ", 
        RowBox[{"k", "/", "r"}]}]]}], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "k"]},
       "Ket"], 
      SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "2"}], "\[Pi]", " ", "\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "x", " ", 
        RowBox[{"k", "/", "r"}]}]]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "65f760fe-5d72-4364-b29e-27a5115ff6ca"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2124460775,ExpressionUUID->"5c234ef0-1a78-4c6b-a105-2b1d3df07ad9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In other words, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "k"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "db5f5f1d-7c30-49d4-9ac5-6ae6036cf1b5"],
 " is an eigenstate of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["U", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e6974f6b-8ef0-4d6c-b864-3ba3f499607b"],
 " belonging to the eigenvalue ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", "2"}], "\[Pi]", " ", "\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "x", " ", 
     RowBox[{"k", "/", "r"}]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "094677d1-f021-422b-935c-9afdaf2de5aa"],
 ". Therefore, by preparing the target register in one of those eigenstates \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "k"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3ea310e5-58af-4316-8457-2fe8d405b437"],
 " and applying the standard quantum phase estimation procedure, one would be \
able to estimate the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]phase\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", 
     SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "k"]}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", 
     RowBox[{"k", "/", "r"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bb1327ec-e0c1-4c64-a027-9d4b0571346c"],
 ". One would then find the order ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["r", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "88ac1ba4-f76a-4cd4-a22f-5a246b1f8845"],
 " from it."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1749130403,ExpressionUUID->"265c1638-432e-406b-88a8-fe4c901c2260"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tUnfortunately, it is highly non-trivial to prepare an register in one of \
those eigenstates. Instead, we prepare the target register in a superposition \
of all eigenstates. This practice is in accordance with a common dictum in \
physics that a localized distribution in real space spreads out in the \
Fourier space and ",
 StyleBox["vice versa",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". Indeed, we find that"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->731039438,ExpressionUUID->"b2a9e602-fde8-4f6f-afd1-8f8eaf994df1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     UnderoverscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
      RowBox[{"k", "=", "0"}], 
      RowBox[{"r", "-", "1"}]], 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "k"]},
      "Ket"]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"1"},
      "Ket"], "\[Congruent]", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"0"},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", "\[CenterEllipsis]", "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{"0"},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{"1"},
       "Ket"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2326ce90-abfc-43cc-9cd9-0c12c547550b"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->825889979,ExpressionUUID->"9ddacad2-77de-4d6f-ac08-1f334f635afe"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which is straightforward to prepare. The cost is that the quantum phase \
estimation procedure randomly selects one from the possible values ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", "r"}], ",", " ", "\[Ellipsis]", " ", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"r", " ", "\[Minus]", " ", "1"}], ")"}], "/", "r"}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"3b6daf1e-2477-43e4-8f47-ab4149a926bd"],
 ". Furthermore, the estimated phase \[Phi] is only approximate to one of the \
precise values ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "k"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"k", "/", "r"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "96d1eadc-5f32-410e-8f9c-1df2eaed139e"],
 ". However, we can overcome these difficulties using the same (classical) \
post-processing as in in the ",
 ButtonBox["period-finding algorithm",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/PeriodFindingAlgorithm#667404647"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1546066492,ExpressionUUID->"c630dd83-7324-4d56-a555-7c70786c1cf6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tThere still remains a question when it comes to the performance of the \
order-finding algorithm. The performance of the algorithm relies on how \
efficiently one can perform the controlled-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["U", 
    SuperscriptBox["2", "k"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "03a7e770-620c-4ea8-8898-452cafed3e25"],
 " gate (see ",
 ButtonBox["Quantum Phase Estimation",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/QuantumPhaseEstimation"],
 "). As mentioned above, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["U", "x"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "eaafad5f-360f-4c36-b565-f96669c1b63e"],
 " is nothing but the quantum-adapted modular exponentiation, and can be \
implemented efficiently on a quantum computer. "
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->187402344,ExpressionUUID->"b7d3dc90-da99-4747-97e3-7251dd3db6dd"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Demonstration", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->1670371837,ExpressionUUID->"cc67e3e1-85d4-4dac-95a6-a96d097af7f4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Make sure that the ",
 ButtonBox["Q3: Symbolic Quantum Simulation",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/guide/Q3"],
 " package is loaded to use the demonstrations in this documentation:"
}], "TechNoteMathCaption",
 CellID->1428640008,ExpressionUUID->"942a477d-58ca-4d52-a317-1ee1da6b0781"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<QuantumMob`Q3`\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:=",
 CellID->853967906,ExpressionUUID->"e540e742-8431-4f5d-8c66-9adda1f96dff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Refer to the \"probe\" and \"system\" registers by symbols ",
 StyleBox["S", "Input"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["T", "Input"],
 ", respectively:"
}], "TechNoteMathCaption",
 CellID->287382804,ExpressionUUID->"1cedfc9d-afd6-473c-a1fa-1dd71b5aa159"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Let", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Qubit", ",", "S", ",", "T"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[5]:=",
 CellID->2082528013,ExpressionUUID->"af6c3027-5b1c-4d47-86ec-02aa09694143"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Suppose that the probe and system registers consist of ",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " qubits, respectively."
}], "TechNoteMathCaption",
 CellID->1039915488,ExpressionUUID->"529b5a05-1466-4f81-be9d-d3720faad70e"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"$m", "=", "4"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"$n", "=", "4"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"jj", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Range", "[", "$m", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"kk", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Range", "[", "$n", "]"}]}], ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[6]:=",
 CellID->1423940154,ExpressionUUID->"020444b0-5404-4bde-9d00-0fb89cf8323c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We are interested in the order of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"a", "=", "3"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d8f5b02c-274b-4ecc-889e-ac7c0066b85a"],
 " modulo ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"N", "=", "16"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "aa405e83-e6c6-408c-bfd3-4111ecb70620"],
 ". (In any realistic calculations, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6176c210-16ba-4a6a-a62a-69714704abdb"],
 " is supposed to be much smaller than ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["2", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "720845f3-614f-46b2-a39d-9e164669a4da"],
 ". In this demonstration, we take ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"N", "=", 
    SuperscriptBox["2", "n"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "18d6f73c-df7a-41d0-b54d-688b9dce8c5e"],
 ".)"
}], "TechNoteMathCaption",
 CellID->1162005408,ExpressionUUID->"a41a1a4a-0fd7-4617-8476-4094722a7a03"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"$N", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Power", "[", 
    RowBox[{"2", ",", "$n"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"$a", "=", "3"}], ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[10]:=",
 CellID->1706524281,ExpressionUUID->"3969b0eb-aa4b-411b-a038-2f23c36a4d77"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Construc the overall quantum circuit to find the order of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["a", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c9f9992e-f915-4537-8004-f1480f914c72"],
 " modulo ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cb3ffad8-9cc6-42f5-862d-a74eb80beeec"],
 ":"
}], "TechNoteMathCaption",
 CellID->716501745,ExpressionUUID->"7bfe0dd0-d896-4153-9c8d-86e889b0a12b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"qc", "=", 
  RowBox[{"QuantumCircuit", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Ket", "[", 
     RowBox[{"S", "@", "jj"}], "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"Ket", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"T", "@", "kk"}], "->", 
      RowBox[{"IntegerDigits", "[", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "$n"}], "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"S", "[", 
     RowBox[{"jj", ",", "6"}], "]"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"ControlledPower", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"S", "[", "jj", "]"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"ModMultiply", "[", 
       RowBox[{"$N", ",", "$a", ",", 
        RowBox[{"T", "[", "kk", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"QFT", "[", 
     RowBox[{"S", "@", "jj"}], "]"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<Invisible\>\"", "->", 
     RowBox[{"S", "[", 
      RowBox[{"$m", "+", 
       RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]}], "]"}]}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[12]:=",
 CellID->1550870118,ExpressionUUID->"0a9d0c12-ceb5-40de-a0f8-11967360d146"],

